This enumeration contains types of symbols which are emitted from the tokenizer. From what I can tell, these are the one-to-one symbols. In other words, while they may be defined as a "type" in the lexer, their purpose is more explicit, whereas the typical "type" rules may not apply.

Some of these symbols may overlap with token types. It seems that if the symbols are optional in coffee-script, they're simply passed out as the type.
